Senior Developer (Dynamics)
As a Senior Developer (Dynamics) you will ensure that high quality Microsoft Dynamics technology solutions are designed, developed and delivered to meet user needs as part of the design of the firms information services, and that they are integrated as part of the overall digital ecosystem supporting development, construction and operation of the project.
About the role:
Provide technical assurance of and if necessary assist the Solutions Architects in the design of technology solutions, based on MS Dynamics, to ensure new or changed services meet user needs and the needs of our technology and service strategies Lead the internal MS Dynamics developments and work with delivery teams, partners and suppliers where necessary to ensure that solutions being developed are robust, scalable and secure with the appropriate overall system design and integration points/APIs, to deliver a high quality user experience Oversee external development services and lead, support and mentor other software development staff on MS Dynamics technologies Ensure delivery teams, development partners and suppliers comply with company technology strategy, MS Dynamics CRM development guidelines and standards, including key technology principles and roadmaps Ensure information technology solutions are integrated to form a digital ecosystem delivering a great user experience Analyse and understand specific project and organisation requirements and provide time and effort estimates for implementation of business requirements Work as part of a team or independently (depending on the size of the project) to undertake development, testing and implementation of MS Dynamics applications to meet specific project requirements Provide and maintain technical documentation for MS Dynamics solutions created / modified or maintained Support, maintain and enhance existing applications developed on MS Dynamics Promote best practices in software development on the MS Dynamics platform and work with the team to fine tune and optimise processes Specify, build and maintain development, test and production software environments Lead the resolution of technology issues arising in delivery and operation of applications developed on MS Dynamics Assist with building a culture of continuous delivery and improvement, ensuring that key systems are regularly analysed, maintained and improved Understand and manage system quality with regards to accessibility, simplicity, usability, availability and security. Qualifications
About You:
Commercial experience of software development on Microsoft Dynamics CRM technologies Experience of developing solutions on MS Dynamics 365 and experience of products including but not limited to CRM, AX & NAV Experience of MS Dynamics 365 applications and creation of custom apps and experience of upgrading to MS Dynamics 365 Good understanding of the Common Data Service for apps Experience of REST API and integrating with SharePoint Online Some exposure to connecting with other Office 365 products such as Power BI Understanding of software development lifecycle Demonstrable ability to work as part of a development team Highly tuned analytical and problem solving skills Excellent communication and interpersonal skills to deal with staff in a variety of disciplines and seniority Experience of working directly with the business stakeholders to gather requirements Keeping up to date with the latest advances/trends in MS Dynamics technology Demonstrable experience of delivering technology solutions based on the leading and emerging technologies Hands-on experience of developing projects using a variety of methodologies including Waterfall and Agile Experience of working on Systems Integration projects either with ERP/CRM/Project Controls would be useful SFIA skills. Government Digital Services framework and service design standards Public and private Cloud service architectures, including G-Cloud Microsoft Azure platform and associated infrastructure architecture Service Oriented Architecture (SOA), Microservices, web services, including JSON and XML Variety of databases and programming languages, e.g. SQL Server, .NET, C#, Java Latest information technologies including their pros and cons in the context of large organisations Integration Architectures and patterns, including knowledge of Enterprise Service Bus Please contact |
